        <h2><span class="emoji">üèÅ</span> 1. Getting Started with Python</h2>
        
        <h3>What is Python?</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Python is a high-level, interpreted programming language.</li>
          <li>Known for readability, versatility, and a large community.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Setting Up Your Environment</h3>
        <ol>
          <li>Install <strong>Python</strong> from <a href="https://www.python.org/downloads/">python.org</a>.</li>
          <li>Choose an IDE:
            <ul>
              <li><a href="https://code.visualstudio.com/">VS Code</a></li>
              <li><a href="https://www.jetbrains.com/pycharm/">PyCharm</a></li>
              <li><a href="https://jupyter.org/install">Jupyter Notebook</a></li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>Test your installation:
            <pre>python --version</pre>
          </li>
        </ol>

        <h3>Running Your First Script</h3>
        <ol>
          <li>Open your IDE or terminal.</li>
          <li>Create a new file <code>hello.py</code>.</li>
          <li>Type the following:
            <pre>print("Hello, Python!")</pre>
          </li>
          <li>Run the script and see the output.</li>
        </ol>

